net.semanticmetadata.lire.indexing

Class MetricSpacesInvertedListIndexing

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.semanticmetadata.lire.indexing.MetricSpacesInvertedListIndexing

  • public class MetricSpacesInvertedListIndexing
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides an indexing approach for approximate search based on the work of G. Amato (giuseppe.amato@isti.cnr.it). See also his paper "Approximate Similarity Search in Metric Spaces using Inverted Files" Date: 14.05.2009 Time: 14:22:03
    Author:
    Mathias Lux, mathias@juggle.at

      • getDefaultInstance

      • createIndex

        public void createIndex(java.lang.String indexPath)
                 throws java.io.IOException
        Creates a set of reference objects and stores it in a new index (hashFunctionsFileName "-ro"). Then creates ordered lists of reference object positions for each data item in the index with given feature. Finally a new index (hashFunctionsFileName "-ms") is created where all the original documents as well as the new data are stored.
        Parameters:
        indexPath - the path to the original index
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • updateIndex

        public void updateIndex(java.lang.String indexPath)
                 throws java.io.IOException
        We assume that the initial indexing has been done and a set of reference objects has been found and indexed in the separate fileList. However further documents were added and they now need to get a ranked list of reference objects. So we (i) get all these new documents missing the field "ro-order" and (ii) add this field.
        Parameters:
        indexPath - the index to update
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
